{
  "stem": "4226.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 189,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the-- high schools, you couldn't feel it so much.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 189,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But universities was limited.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 189,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Jewish people could only attend, I think, 6% of the total.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 189,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was already [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] before the war, even.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 189,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Hungarians introduced that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 190,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 191,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not-- we didn't, we didn't sense-- not all the teachers were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 192,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had non-Jewish teachers as well.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 192,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, we had Romanian teachers, and one Hungarian teacher for gymnastics and physical culture, and a Romanian one for music.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 192,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All the rest were Jewish teachers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 193,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1938, it was Romanian.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 193,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In 1940, it became Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 193,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And parts of the curriculum which we went through in 1938, we had to repeat three, four years later because it was a different curriculum under Hungarian system, especially languages.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 194,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 195,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I do.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 196,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My parents spoke Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 197,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They know, but they couldn't-- they didn't speak properly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 198,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Correct.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 199,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's common.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 199,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You had-- you had certain villages that were pure Hungarian population in Romania.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 200,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's even now the same.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 200,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They've got 2 and 1/2 million Hungarians living there today.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 201,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I do.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 201,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First, we had some fights in the street, daytime.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 201,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 202,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Personally and others from the classroom, from school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 202,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had uniforms.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 202,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And marked-- we had distinguished caps, each school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 203,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So if, if one of us was attacked because he went in a street-- side street-- on his own, and he had other high school students from another school who were beating him up.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 203,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Or if we were more than one, then they wouldn't touch.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 203,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So they picked on a single student.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 204,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They picked on, on single ones, which they were sure they could beat him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 205,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was non-Jewish children walking the street.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 205,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They'd pick on a Jewish child walking alone.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
